Description: Fragment of nearly rectangular handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine buff-brown; some grog; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Sostratos. Probable same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 181, 3. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0213.08.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0844)
